    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> | (<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>)</placeName>
                    <date>July 13<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1881</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I thank you for your extremely kind letter of the 8<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. &amp; for your essay on climates, which I shall be very glad to read, as I well remember the interest which your original memoir caused me.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I thank you, also, for your photograph which I have added to my collection,<ref target="#foot.f2"/> &amp; have much pleasure in sending you my own.—</p>
<p>With all good wishes, believe me, Dear Sir, yours faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway … S.E.R.</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Blytt’s <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13237.xml" resp="#mjhawkins" cert="high">letter of 8 July 1881</ref> has not been found. There is a copy of Blytt’s paper ‘Die Theorie der wechselnden kontinentalen und insularen Klimate’ (The theory of changing continental and insular climates; <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9829.xml">Blytt 1882</ref>) in the Darwin Pamphlet Collection–CUL. Blytt’s original memoir was his <hi rend="italic">Essay on the immigration of the Norwegian flora during alternating rainy and dry periods</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9011.xml">Blytt 1876</ref>); see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 24, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10433.xml">letter to Axel Blytt, 28 March 1876</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Blytt’s photograph has not been found in the Darwin Archive–CUL.</note>
        </div>
    
